<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,937]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,342,296,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Male. Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[359,487,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1268,1291]" captionTargetBox="[200,1365,176,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,145,1247]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Psilochlorops, head, dorsal and lateral view. 1, 7. Psilochlorops clavitibia (holotype). 2, 8. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 3, 9. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 4, 10. Psilochlorops paganelliae (holotype), sp. n. 5, 11. Psilochlorops elongatum (paratype), sp. n. 6, 12. Psilochlorops flavisoma (holotype), sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214703/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Figs. 4, 10</figureCitation>
). Yellow, slightly wider than thorax, broader than long in dorsal view, higher than wide in lateral view; frontal triangle pale brown, margins at most gently curved, reaching anterior margin of frons; occiput dark, bare; gena and postgena with same width, about 
<number box="[870,919,367,391]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="0.33">0.33</number>
eye height; eye rounded, long axis diagonal; clypeus yellow; labella yellow; palpus yellow. First flagellomere dark yellow, with brownish areas on distal margin; arista light brown. One row of interfrontals external to frontal triangle; postocellars convergent; inner and outer verticals well–developed; one row of setulae at lower margin of gena, without a distinct vibrissa. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1347,1435,476,500]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,255,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[197,1394,607,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,574,1926]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Psilochlorops, mesonotum, dorsal view. 13. Psilochlorops clavitibia (holotype). 14. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 15. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 16. Psilochlorops paganelliae (holotype), sp. n. 17. Psilochlorops elongatum (paratype), sp. n. 18. Psilochlorops flavisoma (paratype), sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214704/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Figs. 16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[269,300,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 27" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1984,2007]" captionTargetBox="[186,1410,1106,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1061,1963]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 27. Psilochlorops paganelliae, sp. n. 25. Habitus (paratype). 26. Male terminalia, ventral view (holotype). 27. Epandrium, dorsal view (holotype). Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214707/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">25</figureCitation>
). Scutum almost twice as long as broad, mainly yellowish, with five dark brown stripes, with dark pilosity; scutellum yellow. Pleura yellowish, post–pronotum with a small orange marking, with two bristles. Brownish, elongated markings on anepisternum and notopleura, a dark brown marking on ventral margin of katepisternum. Halter whith yellow stem, pale yellow knob. Legs dark yellow, light brownish on mid and hind femora and tibiae, tibial organ pale yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[608,672,655,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Wing</emphasis>
. Hyaline. Costal sections one to four: 
<date box="[1117,1236,655,679]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="1919-03-19" valueMax="1919-03-08" valueMin="1919-03-19">
<number box="[1117,1147,655,679]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="19.0">19</number>
- 
<number box="[1157,1187,655,679]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="19.0">19</number>
- 
<number box="[1196,1210,655,679]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="8.0">8</number>
- 
<number box="[1219,1233,655,679]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="3.0">3</number>
.
</date>
R 
<number box="[1264,1272,671,685]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1281,1288,671,685]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="3.0">3</number>
slightly concave; R 
<number box="[238,246,710,724]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[255,262,710,724]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="5.0">5</number>
straight; R 
<number box="[387,395,710,724]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[404,411,710,724]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[491,497,710,724]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[506,515,710,724]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
rather divergent; M 
<number box="[746,752,710,724]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[761,770,710,724]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
straight; r-m and dm-cu parallel, distant each other 2.0 as long as dm-cu. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[324,440,733,758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[457,541,733,757]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 27" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1984,2007]" captionTargetBox="[186,1410,1106,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1061,1963]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 27. Psilochlorops paganelliae, sp. n. 25. Habitus (paratype). 26. Male terminalia, ventral view (holotype). 27. Epandrium, dorsal view (holotype). Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214707/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[510,541,733,757]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergites light brown, with distal margin yellowish, sternites light yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Hypandrium with triangular apical extensions (
<figureCitation box="[789,874,769,793]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 27" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1984,2007]" captionTargetBox="[186,1410,1106,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1061,1963]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 27. Psilochlorops paganelliae, sp. n. 25. Habitus (paratype). 26. Male terminalia, ventral view (holotype). 27. Epandrium, dorsal view (holotype). Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214707/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[842,874,769,793]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrium without ventral projections; mesolobus rectangular, weakly sclerotized; surstylus short, partially fused to epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[1068,1152,805,829]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 27" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1984,2007]" captionTargetBox="[186,1410,1106,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1061,1963]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 27. Psilochlorops paganelliae, sp. n. 25. Habitus (paratype). 26. Male terminalia, ventral view (holotype). 27. Epandrium, dorsal view (holotype). Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214707/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[1120,1152,805,829]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="27.0">27</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,937]" box="[201,402,841,866]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,295,842,866]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Female.</emphasis>
As male.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,937]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,337,877,902]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[638,776,878,902]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Psilochlorops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavisoma">
<emphasis box="[638,776,878,902]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">P. flavisoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be rather easily differentiated by the dark brown ventral mark on the katepisternum, and shape of the epandrium, without the long ventral projections distally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
